<p>Wednesday 3rd October 1917</p>
<p>Nr Reninghelst<br/>Raining very heavy.<br/>2.30am pulled out of bed and had to harness up read to move out by 3.30am (4 teams going out) Arr.Berna Hill Dump  (on outside of Ypres) about 5.30am Carting empty ammunition boxes from there to Howe Dump. Done three trips arrived back in lines about 3pm.Fritz sending over liquid fire shells about a mile to the right of us.</p>
